## Actions
1. Add one sentence to A.5 reporting the a-priori null-model result: when
   the three traditions are fixed a priori from the historical record
   (@tbl-traditions authors) with no community detection, the observed
   within-tradition co-citation share (0.85) and 3-partition modularity
   (0.17) still exceed a degree-preserving configuration-model null
   (0.61 / -0.04; z ≈ 6-7, p ≈ 0.001, N = 1000), so the pre-2007
   separation survives conditioning on the graph's sparsity even when the
   labelling is kept clean of the graph's own structure. Do NOT lead with
   the Louvain-anchored numbers (z ≈ 26) — that partition is fitted to the
   graph the null tests, so it overstates the historical claim.
2. State the separation honestly as real but modest: the a-priori effect
   is much weaker than the fitted-partition figure. Avoid "~26 sd".
3. Cite the numbers by provenance (regenerable Make target + config seed),
   not as free-floating figures — per the manuscript-number provenance norm.
4. Keep the HET register; state what the test shows, not method jargon.

